{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
There is also a large literature analyzing differences between nonprofit and for-profit health plans. Deriving generalized conclusions from these studies is difficult because much depends on how one defines \u8220\'3fcommunity benefits\u8221\'3f and \u8220\'3fhealth plans.\u8221\'3f However, as a general matter, they illustrate some significant differences between nonprofit and for-profit HMOs in the extent to which they provide broadly-defined community benefits. As to health insurers, there is little evidence that the nonprofit form makes a positive difference for the communities in which they operate.
\par 
