{\super \b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
126
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Until recently, however, courts and charitable regulators have paid remarkably little attention to the key mechanisms affecting accountability. As Part II describes, state attorneys general have brought dozens of cases in recent years that implicate these issues in contexts ranging from unvarnished corruption to business reorganizations necessitated by changing economic conditions. But the glare of the spotlight has only highlighted the manifold inadequacies of legal doctrine regulating governance of nonprofit organizations.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
