{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EYRBG_2}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EYRBG_2}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
This Part summarizes and criticizes nonprofit corporation law regarding fiduciary duties, which has been a principal tool used by attorneys general in their cases involving the accountability of nonprofit boards. The Part first concludes that corporate fiduciary law is too permissive and uncertain to protect against opportunistic or lax business 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
