*33
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 practices. As is true in the for-profit sector, where market discipline and the possibility of a takeover exerts some pressures, nonprofit corporate law cannot be relied upon to police the activities of nonprofit managers and directors. Second, there is reason to doubt that fiduciary law can ensure that managers and directors remain faithful to the nonprofit\rquote s corporate mission or will be effective in vetting decisions to alter the mission.
\par 
}
}
