{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In the business corporation context, the duty of loyalty flows from the directors\rquote  duty to maximize shareholder wealth. This philosophical underpinning poses obvious difficulty for application to the nonprofit corporation, which does not have shareholders, whose legal form rests on a commitment to a charitable enterprise, and whose mission therefore is not 
}
