{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 In general, the law prohibits only those self-dealing transactions that are not approved or ratified by the board of directors or shareholders under specified standards. In the business corporation context, approval may be gained by the vote of a disinterested majority of the board of directors or by a majority of disinterested shareholders provided the terms of the transaction are fully disclosed prior to the vote.
}
