Finally, we consider the curiously neglected role of institutional mission in informing directors\rquote  duties. Conversions, closures, asset sales, and other organic changes involving nonprofit corporations require directors\rquote  most assiduous adherence to their fiduciary duties. Fiduciary questions arise in many contexts, including whether the conversion or change of purpose is consistent with the purpose of the nonprofit organization; whether the purchaser is appropriate in view of the entity\rquote s charitable purposes; whether directors approving the decision resolved 
