282
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Moreover, interventions that question long-established business structures raise significant policy questions. For example, the demand that Allina spin off its HMO implicates the permissible relationships among the component parts of an integrated delivery system and ultimately whether an integrated delivery system is even possible. Further, the Attorney General\rquote s position in Allina questions whether the corporate purposes of a system member may be subsumed by the system\rquote s over-arching mission.
\par 
}
}
}
