{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EATCI_2}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EATCI_2}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
As a general guiding principle, we suggest that \u8220\'3fmission primacy\u8221\'3f should be recognized as a central objective of the nonprofit enterprise with the corollary that directors enjoy presumptive deference in defining and, within limits, amending that mission. This focus would incorporate mission-centered values into interpretations of the traditional fiduciary duties of care and loyalty. At the same time, like the model of \u8220\'3fdirector primacy\u8221\'3f advanced for proprietary corporations,
}
