{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Where a board\rquote s actions are questioned under duty of care or loyalty standards, mission factors may help give content to the inchoate considerations that contribute to the board\rquote s deliberation. Likewise, mission primacy may compel deference in the economically important cases involving multi-state charitable corporations consolidating their holdings, or whose mission calls for the reallocation of revenues from profit-producing facilities to facilities in financially distressed communities, irrespective of whether such aid crosses state lines.
\par 
}
