 Whatever oversight agenda of the charitable sector a state attorney general decides to pursue, we view it as essential that the office clearly articulate its public policy concerns, expectations, and standards of review. The need for such guidance is particularly acute if attorneys general intend to assert standing on mission issues, for which there is virtually no precedent to guide nonprofit boards.
