{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa200 \sb0 
Several factors contribute to the changing landscape of health care and the increasing need to compete with for-profits. With governmental regulation of the health field receding and market forces becoming dominant, medicine has taken on a primarily business (rather than service) orientation, and the line between the standards governing for-profit and nonprofit enterprises has blurred. David B. Starkweather, Profit Making by Nonprofit Hospitals, in Nonprofit Organizations in a Market Economy 105 (David C. Hammack & Dennis R. Young eds., 1993).
