Fiduciaries are those undertaking a duty to act for the benefit of others as to matters within the scope of their fiduciary relationship. In the context of business associations, fiduciaries (i.e. corporate directors, who are also sometimes confusingly referred to as \u8220\'3ftrustees\u8221\'3f) are held to a good faith standard. James Fishman, 
}
