Mission is little addressed by either the Model Act or the common law. It has long been assumed that a board may alter its mission by amending its articles of incorporation. The process is rather uncomplicated; the Revised Model Act provides that a \u8220\'3fcorporation may amend its articles of incorporation at any time to add or change a provision that is required or permitted in the articles or to delete a provision not required in the articles.\u8221\'3f Id. \u167\'3f 10.01. Nowhere is it suggested that such amendments may not affect the corporate purposes.
