}\b0 \cf22 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 }}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa0 \sb0 
. Both the attorney general and a court must be involved in the disposition of substantially all of the nonprofit\rquote s assets, \u8220\'3fto ensure that the interests of the ultimate beneficiaries of the corporation, the public, are adequately represented and protected from improvident transactions.\u8221\'3f Id. Further, the MEETH court observed that the legislature imposed a higher standard of care upon the director of the nonprofit. 
