 (\u8220\'3fThe manifestation of intention requires an external expression of intention as distinguished from undisclosed intention. There may, however, be a sufficient manifestation of intention to create a trust without communication of that intention to the beneficiary or to the trustee or any third person.\u8221\'3f). By virtue of the restrictions, the donee corporation becomes the trustee obliged to ensure that the property is devoted to the specified purposes. The members of the board of directors are not trustees, in the strict sense, however, because they do not hold title to the property of the corporation. Id. 
